text:
Jacobus Place, south to Leyden Street, showing the incline sweeping up from the ravine carrying the Harlem River, that separates this, Marble Hill, from the Manhattan mainland. On the far side of the river are the grounds containing Columbia's Baker Field. Beyond is the Washington Heights section of the City. The photographers vantage point is the point of convergence of Fort Charles and Van Côrlear Pls.

May 3, 1937

W. P. A., photo
Five Boroughs Project
